com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface NativeMethodSignature

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehaviorSignature
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeInstanceMethodSignature, NativeStaticMethodSignature
public interface NativeMethodSignature
extends NativeBehaviorSignature

The NativeMethodSignature interface represents the native signature declaration of native methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:

Method Detail

decMethod

TypeNativeMethod decMethod(java.lang.Class methodClass)
Declares a native method type using the specified native method class and this signature.

Current implementation is:

return getTypeManager().decMethod(methodClass,this);

Parameters:
methodClass - the native method class or interface to use.
Returns:
the native type of the declaration.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.decMethod(Class,NativeMethodSignature), NativeBehaviorSignature.decBehavior(Class)

newMethodReflection

NativeMethodReflection newMethodReflection(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
Creates a native method reflection wrapper using this signature and the specified method reflection object.

It is implemented calling NativeBehaviorSignature.newBehaviorReflection(Member) with the specified method.

Returns:
a new NativeMethodReflection object as a callback of the specified method.

newDirectMethodCallback

NativeDirectMethodCallback newDirectMethodCallback(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
Creates a new direct method callback of the method defined using the specified java.lang.reflect.Method object.

It is implemented calling NativeBehaviorSignature.newDirectCallback(Member) with the specified method object.

Returns:
a new NativeDirectMethodCallback as a callback of the method defined in the native signature.
